			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, some things obviously need to be clarified. Under normal circumstances, guides / gms CAN NOT be killed.  They have items to prevent it, and they are near immortal.  During GM run quests you are not killing a GM, but a character designed for that event; this character is designed to be killed and isn't a GM at that point but a Player controlled NPC (bit of a contradiction in terms =).  Assuming you actually killed a gm somehow or came across their corpse and found yourself able to loot it, you wouldn't be able to take ANYTHING since all of their items are NO DROP.  And then, assuming that due to a bug you actually did loot a no drop item off them, you would be struck dead as all GM items are designed so that no players can accidentally get them.<BR>
     This hammer would not be a GM item.  One handed out by a GM as part of a quest perhaps, but NOT a GM weapon.  Guides/GMs do not get any useful weapons and armor since they are not allowed to kill things and hunt in the first place.  They have a /kill command to deal with problem NPC's but even that has to be used only as a last resort.<BR>
     Sorry for this long post, but I have gotten sick and tired of people posting things like &quot;my friend killed a GM and now has a ring of fire-and-ice-and-magical-teleporting-kobolds-of-doom&quot; or &quot;GM's get all the best weapons and it isn't fair&quot;.  Remember people, Guides are spending their own free time to help out.<BR>
 <BR>
PS - to all those with dreams of killing a GM on a PvP server:  A group of people tried this when an unlucky guide went linkdead.  THey succeded and were promptly banned 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
